  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed via Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition variability and blood viscosity uncertainty across the five operating points; a screening sensitivity study was also conducted during model development to rank input parameters by their contribution to predicted hemolysis index variance. UQ results confirm that boundary condition uncertainty contributes less than 4% relative variation in RH across all operating conditions, supporting the Accepted decision.",
  "hasUncertaintyQuantification": true,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-rh-criterion",
