      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; turbulence model selection documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published literature demonstrating superior performance for rotating blood pump applications compared to k-epsilon variants. Power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) applied consistently. Model form uncertainty not formally quantified at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs identified and their nominal values documented with sources; input uncertainty ranges specified for UQ.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs documented including pump geometry (from manufacturer CAD), blood analog viscosity (measured at 37°C), inlet velocity profiles (from flow straightener characterization), and rotational speed (encoder measurement). Uncertainty ranges for inlet flow rate (±3%), viscosity (±5%), and rotational speed (±1%) were specified and propagated via Monte Carlo UQ. A screening sensitivity study conducted during model development ranked these inputs; UQ propagation confirmed boundary condition uncertainty contributes less than 4% relative variation in RH. Structured sensitivity analysis linking is not included in this submission package as the screening study was conducted as an informal pre-analysis activity."
    },
