    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 4. UQ results demonstrate that boundary condition and material property uncertainties contribute less than 4% relative variation in the RH metric, well within the margin supporting the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The model is judged credible for the intended use of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. Decision: Accepted.",
